## Session End

```javascript
save_session_state({
  project_id: "{{PROJECT_ID}}",
  current_plan_id: "plan-x",      // if using a plan
  current_task_id: "{{PROJECT_ID_UPPER}}-123",
  kind: "work",                   // work | exploration | qa | throwaway
  working_memory: {
    phase: "Implementation",            // Required
    current_focus: "What you're doing", // Required
    next_action: "Specific next step"   // Required
  },
  context_snapshot: {
    next_session_start: "Clear instruction for next instance",  // Required
    files_modified: ["file.ext:23 (what changed)"],
    tasks_completed: ["{{PROJECT_ID_UPPER}}-123"],
    decisions_made: ["Why you chose X over Y"]
  }
})
```

`kind` classifies the session so noisy exploration / qa / throwaway runs can be filtered out of `get_sessions` and `recent_activity`. Default: `work`.

Save at discrete work units (think git commits). Not after every tool call. Not before you've accomplished anything.

