## Tags & Phase Labels

**Convention:** use task tags to mark logical phases of a multi-phase plan.

When a plan splits into independent phases that ship at different times (e.g., a "renderer" track and a "metrics" track that don't depend on each other), tag tasks accordingly so you can filter / view per phase:

```javascript
// Phase 3a: ASCII renderer
save_task({plan_id: "plan-viz", title: "Renderer foundation", tags: ["3a"]})

// Phase 3b: Estimates + CPM
save_task({plan_id: "plan-viz", title: "Migration for estimates", tags: ["3b"]})

// Filter by phase later
search_tasks({project_id: "{{PROJECT_ID}}", query: "tag:3a"})
```

Tags compose: `["3a", "frontend"]` is a frontend task in phase 3a. Stay terse — `3a` is a phase label, not a free-text description.

